# PDFMark Project Structure Guide

## Main Entry Points
- [app.py](mdc:app.py) - FastAPI web application with modern UI
- [pdf_to_markdown.py](mdc:pdf_to_markdown.py) - Command-line conversion script
- [start_webui.py](mdc:start_webui.py) - Web UI startup script

## Core Components
- [install_requirements.py](mdc:install_requirements.py) - Dependency management
- [README.md](mdc:README.md) - Bilingual project documentation (Chinese/English)

## Directory Structure
- `uploads/` - Temporary file upload directory for web interface
- `outputs/` - Generated Markdown files output directory
- `static/` - Static assets for web interface

## Key Functions
- `extract_text_with_pymupdf()` - PDF text extraction using PyMuPDF
- `detect_headings()` - Intelligent heading detection and hierarchy preservation
- `clean_markdown()` - Format optimization and cleanup

## Technology Stack
- **Backend**: FastAPI, PyMuPDF, PyPDF2
- **Frontend**: HTML/CSS/JavaScript with modern responsive design
- **File Processing**: pandas for data handling
